##WHAT IS CLIPPING? 
Clipping is a method of earning money by creating and posting short-form content (such as Reels or Shorts) from longer videos. In this model, you work on campaigns and get paid based on views.

##BASIC TERMS 
Clipper - 
A clipper is a person who creates and posts short-form clips as part of a campaign and earns money based on the performance of those clips.

Campaign - 
A campaign is a clipping task or opportunity provided by a creator, brand, or platform, where specific content, guidelines, and a payment model are given.

Server / Community - 
A server or community is an online platform—such as Discord or Whop—where clippers join to access campaigns, instructions, and support.
No need for expensive equipment — just a phone/laptop and internet

RPM - 
RPM is a performance-based metric used in clipping campaigns that determines how much a clipper earns for every 1,000 views their content generates.
Example
If RPM = $2
10,000 views → you earn $20

##PROS OF CLIPPING 
No need for expensive equipment — just a phone/laptop and internet.
No need to make content. You repurpose existing long form content 
Work anytime , from anywhere 

##CONS OF CLIPPING 
Many beginner enter this space 
Earning depends on performance 
Some campaigns might have strict rules .
